WEBVTT

00:00.934 --> 00:03.237
Previously on The Riches.

00:03.304 --> 00:05.106
[ Car Crashes ]
[ Tires Screeching ]

00:07.975 --> 00:10.511
- Sorry.
- [ Dahlia ] You wanna
pretend to be the dead guy?

00:10.578 --> 00:12.613
You wanna wear his suits,
and you want me
to be his dead wife?

00:12.680 --> 00:14.682
[ Cael ]
Do you really think
Dad has a plan?

00:14.748 --> 00:20.354
He stole the money. Ma lost
the money. And now we're here
in a dead guy's house.

00:20.421 --> 00:23.591
How'd y'all get
in the front gate?
We live here.

00:23.657 --> 00:26.094
Why are we gettin' a bill from
Mountain View Nursing Home...

00:26.160 --> 00:28.429
for $4,700 a month?

00:28.496 --> 00:30.030
[ Cael ]
Must be where
Cherien's mother is.

00:30.098 --> 00:33.567
- Come on, Ma.
We're getting outta here.
- It's Cherien's mom.

00:33.634 --> 00:35.536
Does it matter?

00:37.004 --> 00:40.208
If my husband's gay?
Doesn't matter to me.

00:40.274 --> 00:42.310
Well, you're not his wife.

00:42.376 --> 00:44.912
- School bus is here!
- [ Bell Ringing ]

00:44.978 --> 00:50.451
Aw, him? Aww.
Got yourself
a buffer boyfriend.

00:50.518 --> 00:53.454
- [ Sniffing ]
- Jesus Christ, Chunky.

00:53.521 --> 00:55.856
What's wrong
with you idiots?
Shut the goddamn door!

00:55.923 --> 00:59.260
I wanted to be a partner.
There is my partner
lying on the ground.

00:59.327 --> 01:01.695
Something about it
makes me sick to my stomach.

01:01.762 --> 01:06.400
I'm not lying, Wayne.
Told you, I'm off that shit.

01:08.502 --> 01:11.539
Oh, no. No, no! No! Hey!
I was gonna flush it!

01:11.605 --> 01:14.408
How big a supply is this?
A month? A week?

01:14.475 --> 01:17.278
No, Wayne-- No! No!
[ Sniffs, Grunts ]

01:17.345 --> 01:18.812
Are you trying to blow
this whole thing to hell?

01:18.879 --> 01:22.816
How do you like it,
watching someone
you love self-destruct?

01:22.883 --> 01:25.286
I've messed up
your whole life.

01:25.353 --> 01:28.322
All I ever wanted was
a messed-up life with you.

01:31.892 --> 01:34.695
[ Wayne Muttering ]

01:41.235 --> 01:43.237
[ Groaning ]
Oh.

01:43.304 --> 01:48.075
Baby, you gotta get up.
Oh, baby.

01:48.142 --> 01:51.111
Oh, baby, you gotta get up,
go to work.

01:51.179 --> 01:53.547
Work?
Yeah.

01:53.614 --> 01:55.749
Let me see.

01:55.816 --> 01:57.718
Oh.
[ Groans ]

01:57.785 --> 02:01.455
Meth hangover's the worst.
It's the worst. You gotta--

02:01.522 --> 02:03.757
You gotta drink
a lot of water.

02:03.824 --> 02:05.693
Come on.

02:05.759 --> 02:09.363
- You still got your job
at Panco, baby.
- Don't want it.

02:09.430 --> 02:13.000
Hugh's an asshole.
Yep, he is.

02:13.066 --> 02:16.270
Now, uh,

02:16.337 --> 02:19.507
I was up all night,
and I've been thinkin'.

02:19.573 --> 02:22.276
I've really been
screwin' things up since
we got here, you know?

02:22.343 --> 02:25.279
And after yesterday, Jesus--

02:25.346 --> 02:27.481
I can't do this anymore
to you and the kids.

02:29.617 --> 02:31.885
This life we got here
is a good thing.

02:31.952 --> 02:35.223
I-I think we just gotta
take it on, you know?
Make it our own.

02:37.124 --> 02:40.228
- Really?
- Sure.

02:40.294 --> 02:44.398
And you know what else
I been thinkin', Wayne?
We need to get us an ishka.

02:44.465 --> 02:48.001
We need to clear
all this shit out
and do a cleansing.

02:48.068 --> 02:50.904
All of us together.
Remember, like that time
in Kentucky...

02:50.971 --> 02:54.342
when we went in the river
with all the snow on the rocks?

02:54.408 --> 02:56.610
- Now?
- Yeah.

02:56.677 --> 02:58.846
I'm sure
there's a cold river
around here somewhere.

02:58.912 --> 03:01.449
No.
Yeah.

03:01.515 --> 03:04.352
Cleansing, baby.
Cleansing.

03:04.418 --> 03:06.487
- Now?
- Yeah.

03:06.554 --> 03:08.989
Oh, come on.
Let's just do it.

03:09.056 --> 03:11.925
- The school bus is gonna
be here any minute.
- I got a math quiz today.

03:11.992 --> 03:14.395
I can't just go
jumpin' in a river. Sorry.
So?

03:14.462 --> 03:18.299
It's library day.
I gotta return my books.
Otherwise, I can't get new ones.

03:18.366 --> 03:20.468
[ Sniffs ]
Banana.

03:20.534 --> 03:22.903
With a bit
of vanilla yogurt.
Oh.

03:22.970 --> 03:25.205
Okay. We'll just
do it later then.
We'll do it after school.

03:25.273 --> 03:26.940
Okay.

03:27.007 --> 03:29.777
[ Whirring ]

03:29.843 --> 03:33.247
[ Shuts Off ]

03:33.314 --> 03:37.551
Okay, look. We-We gotta deal
with the whole Dr. Morganstern
situation, 'cause--

03:37.618 --> 03:40.354
You really miss
all your friends at
the home, don't you, Mama?

03:40.421 --> 03:43.557
She doesn't miss her friends.
She likes it here.

03:43.624 --> 03:45.759
Can we talk about this later?

03:45.826 --> 03:48.161
We're gonna have to
talk about it eventually,
because we can't keep her.

03:48.228 --> 03:49.797
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]
Hey!

03:49.863 --> 03:52.232
- Give me that, you jerk!
Give it!
- It's Eric.

03:52.300 --> 03:54.968
- He wants to know if
you're wearing the shirt.
- [ Sam ] What's the shirt?

03:55.035 --> 03:57.605
Eric bought them both
matching shirts.
It's very cute.

03:57.671 --> 04:01.475
They are not matching, Cael.
They're similar.

04:01.542 --> 04:04.978
- God!
You're such an idiot!
- [ Mouths Words ]

04:05.045 --> 04:07.848
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

04:09.383 --> 04:11.485
Hey, I thought
we had to get to work?

04:11.552 --> 04:13.454
What's wrong with you?

04:16.424 --> 04:18.759
- Oh, Di Di.
- He's such a dick, Mom.

04:18.826 --> 04:21.895
Don't mind him.
I think it's nice
you got a friend.

04:21.962 --> 04:23.731
You do?
Yeah.

04:23.797 --> 04:25.866
It means you're gettin'
adjusted to this place.

04:25.933 --> 04:28.469
I guess.

04:29.737 --> 04:31.872
Hey, I wanna
show you somethin'.

04:34.308 --> 04:36.777
I-- I'm through with it.
See?

04:36.844 --> 04:39.179
I'm through with it--
all of it.

04:39.246 --> 04:41.349
Well, that's--
that's great, Mom.

04:41.415 --> 04:44.017
No, no, I mean it.
Um, I mean it.

04:44.084 --> 04:47.187
Okay.
I don't want you to feel like
you gotta protect me no more.

04:47.254 --> 04:50.123
It's not fair, and, you know,
I'm gonna do it myself.
[ Horn Honking ]

04:50.190 --> 04:51.992
Whatever you say, Mom.

04:52.059 --> 04:54.862
[ Cael ]
School bus is here, Di Di.
Gotta go.

04:54.928 --> 04:56.830
Okay.
Bye.

04:58.999 --> 05:03.437
Hugh's not back yet.
What do you mean,
he's not back yet?

05:03.504 --> 05:05.373
Where is he?
What's he doing?

05:05.439 --> 05:07.975
He told Kimmie he was at
the mortgage brokers'
convention in Reno.

05:08.041 --> 05:10.378
- But when she called the hotel,
he wasn't registered.
- Shit.

05:10.444 --> 05:13.747
He just called
and fired Larry in Legal.
Called him a sniveling dickhead.

05:13.814 --> 05:15.816
Canceled
his company credit card.
You know what?

05:15.883 --> 05:18.051
He did the same thing
to Sabrina in Accounting.
You're kidding.

05:18.118 --> 05:20.654
Now he won't even
answer his phone.
Does he do this often?

05:20.721 --> 05:22.656
Not since I've been here.
It's kinda freakin'
everybody out.

05:22.723 --> 05:24.592
Did you hear about Hugh?
I just did.

05:24.658 --> 05:26.960
Maybe he's having a nervous
breakdown. I had a professor
who did that once.

05:27.027 --> 05:28.729
He ended up naked
on the Golden Gate Bridge.

05:28.796 --> 05:31.164
What if he's under investigation
by the F.B.I. or something?

05:31.231 --> 05:33.934
Let me tell you something.
If anything goes down, I ain't
takin' the rap for Hugh's shit.

05:34.001 --> 05:36.370
- Is Panco going under?
- No, of course it isn't.

05:36.437 --> 05:39.440
I'm sure everything's
gonna be fine. Now, everyone
just go back to work.

05:39.507 --> 05:42.410
I'll go...
make some calls.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.449
You know
what's goin' on here.

05:49.650 --> 05:51.652
Hugh's on a meth bender.

05:51.719 --> 05:54.354
Wayne, the man is
an animal stone-cold sober.

05:54.422 --> 05:57.858
- God knows what kind of mess
he's gonna make for himself.
- I know. We gotta do something.

05:57.925 --> 06:00.961
Well, these people
are panicked.
They need leadership.

06:01.028 --> 06:03.564
You wanna be a partner.

06:05.799 --> 06:07.968
Act like one.

06:09.437 --> 06:12.205
Well, this is what you want,
isn't it?

06:12.272 --> 06:14.608
Is it what you want?

06:16.410 --> 06:21.181
Long as we're here,
if we're gonna stay,

06:21.248 --> 06:23.717
might as well commit,
right?

07:03.491 --> 07:05.559
So there it is.

07:05.626 --> 07:10.531
As of this moment,
I am in control here.

07:10.598 --> 07:12.466
[ Scoffs ]
What are you, General Haig?

07:12.533 --> 07:16.103
I'm the chief
financial officer.
I've been here seven years.

07:16.169 --> 07:18.205
You--
What, seven minutes?

07:18.271 --> 07:20.140
What, uh, makes you the boss?

07:20.207 --> 07:22.175
Well, Mason,

07:22.242 --> 07:28.015
these partnership papers
that I have signed with Hugh.

07:28.081 --> 07:30.651
- May I?
- Absolutely.

07:30.718 --> 07:34.387
So this is the situation.
Hugh, at the moment,

07:34.454 --> 07:39.026
is in a clinic
where he is, uh, undergoing...

07:39.092 --> 07:42.696
intensive Gestalt therapy
designed to purge himself...

07:42.763 --> 07:45.499
of all of his abusive behavior,
which we all know about.

07:45.566 --> 07:48.035
This is a good thing,

07:48.101 --> 07:51.505
and he'll be back very soon,
hopefully better.

07:51.572 --> 07:54.041
Mason.
Thank you.

07:54.107 --> 07:57.477
I welcome your question.
I welcome all your questions.

07:57.545 --> 08:03.350
In fact, my first act
as a partner is to institute
an open-door policy.

08:03.416 --> 08:05.485
Come to me
with your questions.

08:05.553 --> 08:08.088
Just come on in.
Let's have a chat.

08:08.155 --> 08:11.291
Things are gonna go
a little differently
around Panco from now on.

08:11.358 --> 08:14.461
I talked to Hugh last week
about taking tomorrow off.

08:14.528 --> 08:16.597
- I've got finals.
- No problem, Aubrey.

08:16.664 --> 08:18.666
Your dreams are my command.
Great.

08:18.732 --> 08:20.701
I've got crim pro
and real property,

08:20.768 --> 08:23.236
and you know what
a killer that's gonna be.

08:25.138 --> 08:27.307
What?
Oh.

08:27.374 --> 08:28.876
Now that Larry's been fired,

08:28.942 --> 08:31.845
you're gonna have
to take over his cases
until we hire someone new.

08:31.912 --> 08:34.447
Anything pressing?
Nothing much.

08:34.514 --> 08:36.550
A few contracts,
pending settlements. Oh.

08:36.617 --> 08:39.386
You are going to have
to go to court tomorrow
on the Oxenberg case.

08:39.452 --> 08:43.056
Court.
It's a hearing.
It's not a trial or anything.

08:43.123 --> 08:47.595
A nuisance suit against Panco.
A little discrimination thing.
How little?

08:47.661 --> 08:51.498
Hugh intentionally blew
the sale on a house in
the Paradise Grove development.

08:51.565 --> 08:54.467
The couple's
claiming discrimination.
On the basis of what?

08:54.534 --> 08:56.904
They're gay.
Oh.

08:56.970 --> 08:59.673
Larry filed a motion
for summary judgment.

08:59.740 --> 09:03.911
Uh-- Aubrey,
quick snap test.

09:03.977 --> 09:08.682
Summary judgment,
which means we are
going to try to--

09:08.749 --> 09:12.052
Get the suit dismissed.
You will, that is.

09:12.119 --> 09:14.154
I'll be gone, remember?
Finals?

09:14.221 --> 09:17.557
Ah.
Hey, I got an idea.

09:17.625 --> 09:20.060
Call Larry.
Tell him new boss in town.

09:20.127 --> 09:22.362
He's got his job back.
[ Chuckles ]

09:22.429 --> 09:24.064
Larry is too pissed
to go for that.

09:24.131 --> 09:29.169
In fact, I wouldn't be surprised
if he's filing a wrongful
termination suit as we speak.

09:29.236 --> 09:34.675
Well, I am excited by this,
but, uh, it's not my specialty.

09:34.742 --> 09:38.511
You know,
I'm a securities lawyer.

09:38.578 --> 09:42.215
Don't worry.
Larry's done all the work.
All you have to do is show up.

09:43.851 --> 09:47.520
With your experience,
it should be a piece of cake.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.657
Piece of cake.

09:59.900 --> 10:03.003
[ Hartley ]
I don't get many
guests over for dinner.

10:03.070 --> 10:06.473
I used to be real popular
in high school, but lately--
I don't know. Must be the arm.

10:06.539 --> 10:10.644
Oh, yeah?
I'll bet you were
a cheerleader in high school.

10:10.711 --> 10:13.580
I was. How'd you guess?
Well, now, what about you?

10:13.647 --> 10:15.949
What were you
in your teenage years?

10:16.016 --> 10:18.686
I used to start
a lot of fires.

10:20.688 --> 10:22.790
I'm kiddin' ya.
Uh, football.

10:22.856 --> 10:26.694
Quarterback.
Now, see, I knew it.
You got that look.

10:28.428 --> 10:30.463
I'm sorry
to keep you out here.
He just--

10:30.530 --> 10:33.133
He doesn't allow
anybody in the house
while he's watching Jeopardy.

10:35.035 --> 10:37.671
- I think you're pretty.
- Excuse me?

10:37.738 --> 10:41.574
- I said I think
you're pretty, Hartley.
- Be careful now.

10:41.641 --> 10:45.545
Know what I'm gonna do
for you? I'm gonna do all
your landscapin' for free.

10:45.612 --> 10:49.382
I'm gonna cut
them shrubs over there.

10:50.517 --> 10:53.721
[ Buzzer Rings ]
Oh, God.

10:53.787 --> 10:55.856
Is your cake done?

10:55.923 --> 10:58.425
No, that's him.
I can't hire you, Dale.

10:58.491 --> 11:02.129
You need to go.
He can't keep you
in a gilded cage.

11:02.195 --> 11:06.266
Oh, you want to bet?
I got the prenup from hell.

11:06.333 --> 11:09.136
Hugh's had it out for me
since the day I was hired.

11:09.202 --> 11:11.304
Well,
that must be difficult.

11:11.371 --> 11:12.906
But let's look forward.

11:12.973 --> 11:15.408
He threw a cell phone
at my head once...

11:15.475 --> 11:18.278
because he spilled
a glass of water
on his own desk.

11:18.345 --> 11:22.415
That's not good.
Um--

11:22.482 --> 11:26.119
What can we do to make
Panco better for you, Greg?

11:26.186 --> 11:28.789
I'd like my own office.
Right.

11:28.856 --> 11:30.891
And an assistant
would be nice.

11:32.125 --> 11:33.961
Right.

11:34.027 --> 11:38.031
Well, we'll see
what we can do.

11:38.098 --> 11:41.534
- Really?
- Panco does not have
to be run by fear.

11:41.601 --> 11:43.503
We can do better than that.

11:43.570 --> 11:46.639
Smile, Grandma.

11:46.706 --> 11:50.177
This'll help bring
some glow to your face.

11:54.314 --> 11:58.919
You seem like a winter.
Let's try some pink.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.061
You have very
pretty eyes, Grandma.

12:08.128 --> 12:10.998
Mm-hmm.

12:11.064 --> 12:14.001
See, when you accentuate
your best features,

12:14.067 --> 12:17.337
you feel better
about yourself.

12:17.404 --> 12:20.173
I sure do.

12:20.240 --> 12:22.509
Bananas.

12:25.212 --> 12:27.214
I won't let them
take you away in a van.

12:31.484 --> 12:35.222
If they do,
I'll hot-wire a car
and come and get you.

12:37.524 --> 12:39.827
I'll take a large Cadillac.

12:42.996 --> 12:46.967
No, Marcy.
I know it was a bad divorce,
I do. I--

12:47.034 --> 12:50.270
Yeah. Hugh always spoke
very fondly of you.

12:50.337 --> 12:53.773
What can we at Panco
do for you?

12:53.841 --> 12:55.843
A parking space
with my name on it.

12:55.909 --> 12:57.310
Better hold music.

12:57.377 --> 13:00.213
Healthier snacks
in the vending machine.

13:00.280 --> 13:02.182
Okay.

13:02.249 --> 13:06.119
Other companies
give their employees
parking spaces all the time.

13:06.186 --> 13:08.221
- Really?
- A longer lunch break,

13:08.288 --> 13:10.858
'cause I barely have time
to eat my yogurt.

13:10.924 --> 13:13.793
- That seems reasonable.
- I know he's an asshole.

13:13.861 --> 13:17.230
I'm not saying he's not
an asshole. He's just an asshole
who I've gotta find right now.

13:17.297 --> 13:20.200
So I was wondering
if you could-- No--

13:20.267 --> 13:23.270
Just my name.
It doesn't have to be too big.
Just little.

13:23.336 --> 13:25.572
Staff meetings,
'cause we're supposed
to have weekly staff meetings.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.540
I mean,
what happened to them?

13:27.607 --> 13:30.577
- And?
- Hmm?

13:33.013 --> 13:35.448
A-A-A damn parking space.

13:35.515 --> 13:38.318
Huh.

13:38.385 --> 13:40.253
Well, that was pointless.
[ Dahlia ]
All right.

13:40.320 --> 13:45.592
Oh, Jesus!
Well, what's pointless?

13:45.658 --> 13:49.296
Talking to these people.
Whatever happened
to hopes and dreams?

13:49.362 --> 13:51.298
They have no vision.

13:51.364 --> 13:55.502
Their lives have become
so narrow.
It's just working to work.

13:55.568 --> 13:58.705
Wayne, it's pretty hard to have
hopes and dreams when you're
just trying to survive.

13:58.771 --> 14:00.573
You know?
[ Phone Beeping ]

14:01.875 --> 14:04.111
Okay.
Mmm.

14:04.177 --> 14:05.812
Okay.
Let's do the timeline.

14:05.879 --> 14:08.048
Mm-mmm.
Death of Louis XV.

14:08.115 --> 14:12.019
May, 1774.
Mm-hmm.

14:12.085 --> 14:14.888
All right.
King Louis XVI crowned?

14:14.955 --> 14:17.190
June, 1774.

14:17.257 --> 14:19.759
[ Door Closes ]
Ew!

14:19.826 --> 14:21.361
[ Clears Throat ]

14:25.632 --> 14:28.936
- Nice shirt.
- Thanks, dude.

14:30.203 --> 14:33.273
Okay, Eric, let's, uh--
let's keep going.

14:33.340 --> 14:37.110
Uh, King Louis XVI
tried for treason,

14:37.177 --> 14:40.647
and monarchy was abolished--
1792.

14:40.713 --> 14:43.783
And that is when
Marie Antoinette lost her head.
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

14:43.850 --> 14:47.254
You know, that was close,
but actually it was
in 1793.

14:47.320 --> 14:49.856
Hi, Di Di.
Hi, Eric.
Hello.

14:49.923 --> 14:52.692
[ Di Di ]
Hey, Mom.

14:52.759 --> 14:56.129
- You wanna stay for dinner?
- Oh, uh, I would,
but I gotta go.

14:56.196 --> 14:57.998
I told my mom
I'd be back at 5:30.

14:58.065 --> 15:01.268
Wait. I thought you were
gonna help me with
the Reign of Terror, baby.

15:01.334 --> 15:03.436
You know
it's my weakest thing.
You were gonna quiz me.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.572
I can't.
I got my dad's car.
[ Sighs ]

15:05.638 --> 15:09.642
- Well, I can quiz you.
I love history.
- That's okay, Mom. It's fine.

15:09.709 --> 15:11.744
Oh, no.
No, it'll be good. Here.

15:11.811 --> 15:15.682
Um, what was
the initial impact...

15:15.748 --> 15:19.486
of the death
of Lewis X-V-I?

15:19.552 --> 15:21.388
[ Both Chuckling ]

15:23.423 --> 15:25.292
"Lewis X-V-I"?

15:25.358 --> 15:27.927
That's a good one.
[ Dahlia ]
What?

15:27.995 --> 15:30.863
No, never mind, Mom.
It's-- It's no big deal.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.665
It's cool.
What was funny?

15:32.732 --> 15:34.734
Well, it's--
it's Louis XVI,

15:34.801 --> 15:36.469
but, I mean,
don't worry about it.

15:36.536 --> 15:39.172
Come on, Eric.
I'll, uh, walk you out.

15:42.175 --> 15:44.411
See you later, Mrs. Rich.

15:48.048 --> 15:51.284
Bye, Eric.
[ Di Di ]
Shut up, Cael.

15:52.986 --> 15:55.855
Well, Lewis, Louis--
Who gives a shit?

15:55.922 --> 15:59.459
He's a buffer prick, Ma.

15:59.526 --> 16:01.461
[ Scoffs ]

16:01.528 --> 16:03.563
[ Door Closes ]

16:08.235 --> 16:10.637
Gay money, straight money--
What difference does it make?

16:10.703 --> 16:13.973
Well, uh, let me try
to clarify that, Doug.

16:14.041 --> 16:17.710
Five families decide
to buy houses in
a cul-de-sac in Paradise Grove.

16:17.777 --> 16:21.348
Five churchgoing families
who want to create, uh,

16:21.414 --> 16:24.484
a family-value-oriented
community in which
to raise their kids.

16:24.551 --> 16:28.155
- So?
- So they're in escrow, okay?

16:28.221 --> 16:32.425
One day they look over,
and they see two women,

16:32.492 --> 16:35.928
two women in-in-in khakis
and penny loafers...

16:35.995 --> 16:40.200
shakin' hands with the Realtor
in front of the sixth house
of their little cul-de-sac.

16:40.267 --> 16:42.235
Khakis and penny loafers?

16:42.302 --> 16:44.304
It's not that they don't like
gay people, mind you.

16:44.371 --> 16:46.306
They just don't want them
living next door.

16:46.373 --> 16:49.376
So let the churchgoers
move somewhere else.

16:49.442 --> 16:52.512
Well, the problem is-is--
Greg, please.

16:52.579 --> 16:55.315
The problem is,
we've been just
as much a victim...

16:55.382 --> 16:57.317
of the downturn
in the housing market
as anybody.

16:57.384 --> 17:00.053
The houses in Paradise Grove
just aren't selling that well.

17:00.120 --> 17:03.723
We've used some
bullshit collateral to get
our last loan from the bank,

17:03.790 --> 17:07.026
and the only real source
of money to repay those loans...

17:07.094 --> 17:08.895
is from those
five homes in escrow.

17:08.961 --> 17:11.898
And while you're thinking
about it, put this
in your hat and smoke it.

17:11.964 --> 17:14.234
All our loans
are cross-collateralized.

17:14.301 --> 17:17.870
If one loan fails,
the whole house of cards folds.

17:17.937 --> 17:20.840
Meaning Panco?
[ Mason ]
That's right, my friend.

17:20.907 --> 17:23.510
So you ask me what
the difference is between
gay money and straight money--

17:23.576 --> 17:28.381
In this part of the country,
Christian money
begets Christian money,

17:28.448 --> 17:31.118
and gay money
puts you out of business.

17:40.127 --> 17:43.230
Hi, Nina.
Hey, there.
Come on in.

17:43.296 --> 17:45.432
I didn't know
you did pottery.
Yeah.

17:45.498 --> 17:49.302
Um, started as a hobby.
Now it's sort of
taken over my life.

17:49.369 --> 17:51.671
- Hello.
- Hi, there.

17:51.738 --> 17:54.874
Hi, Cherien.
Uh, this is Wes.
Wes, our neighbor Cherien.

17:54.941 --> 17:57.777
Oh, so she's the one--
Uh, yes.

17:57.844 --> 18:00.480
We're on our way to the market.
Need anything, Nina?

18:00.547 --> 18:03.850
Uh, no, thanks.
Well, we'll see you later.

18:03.916 --> 18:06.153
Nice to meet you.

18:07.787 --> 18:11.057
They're making a bouillabaisse
for dinner.

18:11.124 --> 18:13.059
He seems all right.
Wes?

18:13.126 --> 18:15.728
Oh, he is.

18:15.795 --> 18:18.665
Real nice.
Good cook.

18:18.731 --> 18:21.268
So he and Jim are--

18:21.334 --> 18:25.972
Friends. Yeah.
For some time now, it seems.

18:26.038 --> 18:30.577
And you-all just...
hang out together?

18:32.279 --> 18:35.548
Jim and I have been doing
a lot of talking since
your dinner party, Dahlia.

18:35.615 --> 18:37.717
I guess you could say
we've come to an understanding.

18:37.784 --> 18:40.987
Neither of us
wants to downscale
at this stage of our lives,

18:41.053 --> 18:43.055
and there's Zinny
to think about.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.325
So we're sharing the house.

18:46.726 --> 18:50.263
That's about all
we're sharing.
Wow.

18:50.330 --> 18:52.432
Well, I do not know
how you're doin' it.

18:52.499 --> 18:55.802
Weed.

18:55.868 --> 18:58.171
[ Chuckling ]

18:58.238 --> 19:02.141
No.
I got a problem, Nina.

19:02.209 --> 19:03.876
With this?
No.

19:03.943 --> 19:07.314
With Di Di.
I don't know how
to talk to her anymore.

19:07.380 --> 19:09.916
I don't understand.
It's weird.

19:09.982 --> 19:13.420
When they're little,
they just kind of
look up to you.

19:13.486 --> 19:15.755
They wanna dress like you
and be like you.

19:15.822 --> 19:19.058
I mean,
people used to call her
my little twin.

19:19.125 --> 19:21.261
And now she doesn't
want to have nothin'
to do with you.

19:21.328 --> 19:23.263
Yeah.
Yeah.

19:23.330 --> 19:25.765
Well, I'll tell you one thing.

19:28.468 --> 19:31.003
I sure as hell
don't have any answers.

19:31.070 --> 19:36.276
Zinny hasn't been out of
her room except to go to school
since she turned 13.

19:36.343 --> 19:39.246
She is a real bitch.

19:39.312 --> 19:41.881
Most days,
I just leave her alone.

19:41.948 --> 19:43.850
It's either that or kill her.

19:43.916 --> 19:47.320
Oh, God.
I got a big sack of books
if you wanna read 'em.

19:47.387 --> 19:50.790
Maybe you'll have
better luck than I have.

19:52.792 --> 19:54.661
Is that--

19:56.162 --> 19:58.931
It's a lighthouse.

20:02.669 --> 20:04.904
Nice job, Di.

20:04.971 --> 20:06.839
What, Cael?
What?

20:06.906 --> 20:09.342
You've turned into
a total buffer asshole,
that's what.

20:09.409 --> 20:11.644
Why?
Because I actually study?

20:11.711 --> 20:14.180
I don't give a shit
if you study.

20:14.247 --> 20:17.049
Well, what do you think
we're supposed to be
doing here, Cael?

20:17.116 --> 20:19.586
Robbing houses?
No, Di.
I think we're supposed to be...

20:19.652 --> 20:22.789
wearing matching shirts under
our uniforms and thinking
we're better than everyone else.

20:22.855 --> 20:26.726
I do not think
that I am better
than anyone else, Cael.

20:26.793 --> 20:29.429
I'm just trying
to get along here,
and maybe you should try that.

20:31.764 --> 20:34.233
Maybe.

20:34.301 --> 20:37.236
Well, I may not know
so much of law, Mr. Felder,

20:37.304 --> 20:39.606
but I know what's right
and what's wrong.

20:39.672 --> 20:41.941
And I know what
you're asking is wrong.

20:42.008 --> 20:43.943
[ Ringing ]

20:46.479 --> 20:48.180
Hugh.
Doug.

20:48.247 --> 20:50.850
Thank God.
Where are you?

20:50.917 --> 20:55.154
I don't know!
Somewhere in the desert,
I'm guessin'.

20:55.221 --> 20:59.759
Right.
Well, uh, are you okay?
I mean, everybody's worried.

20:59.826 --> 21:04.964
Doug, did you know
that Muslims fast for
the entire month of Ramadan?

21:05.031 --> 21:09.101
But get this.
[ Sighs ]
No, I didn't know that.

21:09.168 --> 21:12.372
Look, I gotta talk to you
about the Oxenberg case, okay?
Get this.

21:12.439 --> 21:16.476
It's not just food
they give up. They give up
all sensual pleasures.

21:16.543 --> 21:19.211
[ Woman ]
Here you are, Mr. Panetta.
And-- Oh. Thank you.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.314
Sex and, you know--
So--

21:21.381 --> 21:23.383
carnal stuff.
So let me get this straight.

21:23.450 --> 21:28.355
You are in the desert
with some Muslims?
No, but I am fasting... I think.

21:28.421 --> 21:33.726
And it's brought me
a shitload of clarity too.
Here, listen to this.

21:33.793 --> 21:38.565
"The candle is not there
to illuminate itself."

21:38.631 --> 21:41.434
Is that heavy or what?
Extraordinarily heavy.

21:41.501 --> 21:44.003
Okay, look, Hugh--
Doug, buddy.

21:44.070 --> 21:47.674
No--
You're my only friend.

21:47.740 --> 21:52.845
You're the only one that gets
this sickness we call life.

21:52.912 --> 21:56.483
Uh-huh. Okay.
Listen-- Listen to me.
Hugh--

21:56.549 --> 21:59.051
Ooh, I'm feelin' a little--
I gotta go.

21:59.118 --> 22:01.120
Doug, I'm gettin'
a little dizzy here.
No--

22:01.187 --> 22:02.789
Hugh--
Ooh.

22:02.855 --> 22:04.391
Hugh? Hugh?
Stay with me!
[ Line Disconnects ]

22:04.457 --> 22:06.058
Goddamn it!

22:14.467 --> 22:17.103
Hey, how's it goin'?

22:17.169 --> 22:19.105
Fine.
Good.

22:19.171 --> 22:21.974
That's good.

22:28.948 --> 22:30.617
What are you doin'?

22:30.683 --> 22:34.854
Well, Di Di,
I just want you to know
that I'm here for you.

22:34.921 --> 22:38.725
If you wanna
talk about anything,
if you feel like sharing--

22:38.791 --> 22:41.160
Sharing what?

22:41.227 --> 22:43.362
Just talking.

22:43.430 --> 22:45.565
Let me know what's
goin' on in your life.

22:46.666 --> 22:49.836
I don't feel like it.

22:49.902 --> 22:52.639
Well, you know,
what-what I'm hearing now
is that...

22:52.705 --> 22:55.207
you're not in the mood
to talk about it right now.

22:55.274 --> 22:58.310
- Yeah, that's--
that's what I'm saying.
- Okay, well, you know what?

22:58.377 --> 23:00.780
That's too damn bad,
because I have something
to say to you, Delilah Malloy.

23:00.847 --> 23:02.715
I don't like the person
you're becoming.

23:02.782 --> 23:06.719
You're turning into a mean,
nasty little bitch, and that
is not the person I raised.

23:06.786 --> 23:08.521
The person
that you raised?

23:08.588 --> 23:11.624
You were in prison.
I was in prison for two years.
I never stopped being your ma.

23:11.691 --> 23:14.160
I took care of everybody--

23:14.226 --> 23:17.329
Dad, Sam, Cael.

23:17.396 --> 23:19.966
And now you what,
you wanna come back
and you wanna be the mom?

23:20.032 --> 23:22.034
I think it's a little bit
late for that.

23:22.101 --> 23:26.706
You know what your problem is?
Is that you're just scared.

23:26.773 --> 23:29.742
You're scared that I'm gonna
be better than you.

23:29.809 --> 23:32.445
Now, I'm gonna go to college,
Mom, and I'm gonna be somebody.

23:32.512 --> 23:34.647
I'm gonna be somebody
that you could never be.

23:34.714 --> 23:39.552
Bullshit.
You know what scares me?

23:39.619 --> 23:41.488
How quickly you've become
one of them buffers.

23:41.554 --> 23:45.191
It's "those" buffers, Mom.

23:45.257 --> 23:49.028
You have completely lost touch
with what's important.
Look at that guy you picked.

23:49.095 --> 23:52.031
He is nothin' more
than a haircut
and a shit-eating grin.

23:52.098 --> 23:54.634
I love him.

23:55.902 --> 24:00.206
You love him?
What does that mean to you?

24:00.272 --> 24:02.675
I'm sleeping with him.

24:06.078 --> 24:07.914
Without a blessing?

24:10.282 --> 24:12.184
Huh.

24:13.786 --> 24:16.989
You're a real
little buffer now.

24:17.056 --> 24:18.958
Congratulations.

24:24.396 --> 24:27.634
Since its inception
nearly 15 years ago,

24:27.700 --> 24:31.103
Panco Properties
has had a history...

24:31.170 --> 24:36.609
of community building
and family values.

24:36.676 --> 24:40.179
We sell to families.
It's what we do.

24:40.246 --> 24:43.583
We sell to
all kinds of families--
red, yellow, black, white--

24:43.650 --> 24:46.653
Are you really gonna say that?

24:46.719 --> 24:48.888
Well, I was thinking of.

24:48.955 --> 24:51.190
That sounds like some kind
of bullshit to me, Wayne.

24:51.257 --> 24:53.526
What's that got to do
with anything anyway?

24:53.593 --> 24:57.396
Well, what am I
supposed to say?
This is about discrimination.

24:57.463 --> 25:01.033
We do not discriminate
under the law.

25:01.100 --> 25:04.837
A gay couple has complained
that Hugh and Panco...

25:04.904 --> 25:08.274
have refused
to sell them their house
because they are gay.

25:08.340 --> 25:12.344
Now, here's the thing.
Gay people are not
specifically protected...

25:12.411 --> 25:14.213
under the Fair Housing Act.

25:14.280 --> 25:16.916
Hugh can absolutely
refuse to sell to them...

25:16.983 --> 25:20.720
and not be breaking
any laws.

25:20.787 --> 25:23.756
And you're gonna stand there
and tell me that that's okay?

25:23.823 --> 25:27.526
Absolutely.
It's completely legal.

25:27.594 --> 25:29.361
Well, no, no.
I mean, it's not okay,

25:29.428 --> 25:32.932
but in this state and in
the whole country as it is,

25:32.999 --> 25:35.001
gay couples are not protected
under the Constitution.

25:35.067 --> 25:37.536
Well, they should be.
Well, that's not the point!

25:37.604 --> 25:40.406
The law is on Hugh's side.
I can win this.

25:40.472 --> 25:43.976
So you're gonna walk
into court tomorrow,
and you are gonna defend...

25:44.043 --> 25:47.179
Hugh's right to be
a total flamin' asshole?

25:47.246 --> 25:50.850
Yeah. That is what
is so great about the law.

25:50.917 --> 25:56.122
Well, that makes you
an asshole too, Wayne.

25:56.188 --> 25:59.558
Excluding people?
Oh, my God.
Are you kidding me?

25:59.626 --> 26:02.629
What if that was your child?
Huh?
What if that was your son?

26:05.865 --> 26:08.067
You are no better
than Hugh.

26:08.134 --> 26:13.505
Well, if I don't do it
and Panco collapses,
what are we gonna live on?

26:13.572 --> 26:15.742
Air?

26:18.711 --> 26:21.648
So this is it, huh?

26:25.284 --> 26:27.086
The American dream.

26:31.157 --> 26:33.059
What happened?

26:35.294 --> 26:39.131
This morning,
you were all gung ho
about me stepping up for Hugh,

26:39.198 --> 26:41.634
making a commitment,
showing leadership.

26:41.701 --> 26:43.335
Well, maybe
I changed my mind.

26:45.772 --> 26:48.107
Maybe I thought you were gonna
be better than Hugh.

26:48.174 --> 26:51.243
I am better than Hugh.
I have already
made a difference.

26:55.114 --> 26:57.583
Honey, I'm just
doing my job here.

26:57.650 --> 27:00.787
And, you know, we should
all be pretty damn glad
that I can do it,

27:00.853 --> 27:03.255
because it is not easy.

27:03.322 --> 27:08.761
I gotta go into a real
courtroom tomorrow, argue
in front of a real live judge.

27:08.828 --> 27:11.898
You know what?
I think I'm gonna do okay.

27:11.964 --> 27:16.135
What is the point
if all you're doin' is buying
into their buffer bullshit?

27:16.202 --> 27:20.072
It is not all
black and white.
Not all buffers are bad.

27:20.139 --> 27:22.641
Oh, really? Well,
I'm real glad you think so,

27:22.709 --> 27:24.977
'cause your daughter's
sleepin' with one.

27:29.115 --> 27:31.417
[ Owl Hooting ]

27:40.693 --> 27:42.762
[ Cigarette Sizzles ]

27:53.272 --> 27:55.207
So, Di Di.

27:55.274 --> 27:57.176
Huh?

27:57.243 --> 27:59.178
[ Sighs ]

28:00.646 --> 28:02.581
Here you go, Mom.

28:02.648 --> 28:04.884
You're not Doug.

28:04.951 --> 28:06.986
And you're not my mom.

28:07.053 --> 28:10.022
But we're having fun
with pancakes, aren't we?

28:14.560 --> 28:18.497
- So, baby--
- Yeah, Dad?

28:18.564 --> 28:20.666
Um--

28:20.733 --> 28:24.904
Um-- Got enough money
for lunch?

28:24.971 --> 28:28.440
Yeah. Yeah, you gave me
$10 yesterday, remember?

28:28.507 --> 28:31.110
Right, right, right.
Okay, I gotta go get ready.

28:31.177 --> 28:33.179
Thank you for breakfast.
Okay.

28:33.245 --> 28:35.381
Okay. Di Di?

28:35.447 --> 28:37.349
Dad, we only did it once.

28:37.416 --> 28:40.652
We used protection.
And I don't know how
I feel about it, okay?

28:40.719 --> 28:44.323
Okay, okay.
Great. Good talk.

28:47.193 --> 28:50.997
[ Sighs ]
That wasn't so hard.

28:51.063 --> 28:53.265
Don't know what
I was worried about.

28:53.332 --> 28:55.434
I made some calls.

28:55.501 --> 28:57.804
Anyone I know?

29:03.709 --> 29:07.746
[ Alarm Chiming ]

29:12.518 --> 29:14.854
Well, I had
a chat with Di Di.

29:17.356 --> 29:20.726
It seems she and Eric
had sex once,

29:20.793 --> 29:24.964
and she used, um,
you know, birth control.

29:29.068 --> 29:31.270
It made me feel better.

29:33.639 --> 29:35.407
We had sex
when you were 15.

29:37.209 --> 29:40.012
We were married, Wayne.
We were in love.

29:40.079 --> 29:42.714
She didn't even
talk to us.

29:42.781 --> 29:46.318
She didn't get no blessing.

29:46.385 --> 29:48.988
I have no idea
who that girl has become.

29:49.055 --> 29:52.624
Well, she's living here now.

29:52.691 --> 29:56.695
If we were living back there,
she'd probably be married
to that idiot and pregnant.

29:56.762 --> 29:59.265
Is that what we want?

30:01.868 --> 30:04.570
Baby, you're taking this
too hard.

30:04.636 --> 30:08.540
Di Di is still Di Di.

30:08.607 --> 30:12.744
No matter what
she says or doesn't say,
she still needs you.

30:12.811 --> 30:14.813
And I need you too.

30:14.881 --> 30:19.018
I've got the whole
of Panco in my hands.
I can't do this without you.

30:22.354 --> 30:24.523
Well, I'm still here,
ain't I?

30:28.127 --> 30:30.162
[ Engine Starts ]

31:18.244 --> 31:20.212
Boo!

31:28.820 --> 31:30.689
Where's Aubrey?
I need Aubrey.

31:30.756 --> 31:33.725
Finals.
Right. Damn!

31:33.792 --> 31:37.029
- Anyone hear from Hugh?
- No, but there are some people
waiting in your office.

31:37.096 --> 31:39.098
Who is waiting
in my office?

31:39.165 --> 31:41.100
I think they said
their name was "Mockingbird."

31:41.167 --> 31:43.635
Doug, Doug.
I know you promised Greg
his own office,

31:43.702 --> 31:45.804
but I actually have
more seniority than he does.

31:45.871 --> 31:48.507
All right, well,
you get an office too.
We don't have the space.

31:48.574 --> 31:51.443
All right, well,
no one gets an office.
What? That's bullshit!

31:51.510 --> 31:53.445
[ Sighs ]

31:56.148 --> 31:58.250
I'm Liz Oxenberg.

31:58.317 --> 32:00.719
Oxenberg.

32:00.786 --> 32:04.523
Yes, that Oxenberg.

32:10.796 --> 32:13.465
Hello.
This is Max.

32:13.532 --> 32:15.401
Hi, Max.
Hi.

32:16.602 --> 32:18.737
Gwen doesn't know I'm here.

32:18.804 --> 32:21.340
She'd kill me
if she did.

32:21.407 --> 32:24.043
I just wanted to see
the face behind Panco.

32:24.110 --> 32:25.711
Well, I'm hardly
the face behind Panco.

32:25.777 --> 32:28.780
I didn't even want that
piece of shit house originally.
It's too small.

32:28.847 --> 32:30.849
The construction is crap.

32:30.916 --> 32:33.319
Doesn't have
much of a backyard.

32:33.385 --> 32:37.689
So why--
Because it's all we could
afford on both our salaries.

32:37.756 --> 32:42.161
And it's in the best
public school system in Ducaine.
We wanted that for Max,

32:42.228 --> 32:46.232
even if it meant
we had to live next door
to a bunch of homophobic bigots.

32:46.298 --> 32:48.334
They didn't even
give us a chance.

32:48.400 --> 32:51.470
We're not worthy
of their cul-de-sac.

32:53.105 --> 32:57.709
Guys like you are lucky.
You will never experience
what that feels like.

33:00.179 --> 33:03.115
See you in court,
Mr. Rich.

33:03.182 --> 33:05.317
Come on, Max.

33:10.089 --> 33:12.058
[ Door Closes ]

33:12.124 --> 33:14.260
[ Knocking ]

33:14.326 --> 33:18.097
- Can I talk to you, Doug?
- Now is not a good time.

33:19.798 --> 33:21.867
I sit next to Tony,
as you know.

33:21.933 --> 33:25.237
And lately,
I've noticed he's been making
a lot of personal calls.

33:25.304 --> 33:27.673
Long-distance personal calls.
I just--

33:27.739 --> 33:31.477
Write it up and
we will talk about it later.

33:32.678 --> 33:35.647
Well, I just know
Hugh wouldn't like it.

33:35.714 --> 33:38.750
Ashleigh, try Hugh's
cell number again and keep
trying until he answers.

33:38.817 --> 33:42.954
And then?
And then I'll
talk to him, sweetheart.

33:43.021 --> 33:45.391
[ Knocking ]
What?

33:45.457 --> 33:49.661
Was Greg just in here ratting
me out just because he's pissed
about the whole office thing?

33:49.728 --> 33:52.331
What a freakin' wuss.
You know what you need to do?
Give him--

33:52.398 --> 33:54.166
What I need to do is work!

33:54.233 --> 33:58.270
So what I need you to do
is to get out of
the goddamn office, Tony!

33:59.471 --> 34:03.041
All of you,
stay out of my office!

34:03.109 --> 34:06.112
I am working!

34:06.178 --> 34:08.414
I have to be in court today.

34:08.480 --> 34:10.749
Do you have to be
in court today?

34:10.816 --> 34:13.385
Thank you.

34:18.824 --> 34:22.027
Just stay out--
Wow.

34:22.094 --> 34:26.532
Didn't take you long to turn
into one of them screamers.
They won't leave me alone.

34:26.598 --> 34:29.701
I'm just sayin', Wayne.
You're scarin' me.

34:31.137 --> 34:33.605
I got him.
He's on line one.

34:33.672 --> 34:35.807
Thank you.

34:35.874 --> 34:38.777
Hugh?
What do you want, Doug?

34:38.844 --> 34:42.481
Tryin' to relax here.
Hugh, uh, you still
with the Muslims?

34:42.548 --> 34:45.617
What the hell
are you talkin' about?

34:45.684 --> 34:49.855
Hugh, I gotta talk to you
about the Oxenberg hearing
today, okay?

34:49.921 --> 34:53.759
Oxenberg?
Yeah, you know,
the Paradise Grove thing.

34:53.825 --> 34:57.496
Oh! The carpet munchers.
What's the problem?

34:57.563 --> 35:00.466
Pretty clear-cut case,
ain't it?
Well, yeah.

35:00.532 --> 35:02.968
Legally, absolutely.
Clear-cut case. But--

35:03.034 --> 35:05.971
Aw, Jesus Christ.
Don't start with
the morals crap.

35:06.037 --> 35:08.340
You're a lawyer.
You don't have morals.

35:08.407 --> 35:11.477
Oh, not my face too, darlin'.
That stuff smells like shit.

35:11.543 --> 35:13.945
No, hang on.
Here-- Here's the point.

35:14.012 --> 35:17.015
On this Oxenberg thing,
it's just business.
It ain't personal.

35:17.082 --> 35:21.253
I don't have a problem
with gays, but--
Here. Look at it this way.

35:21.320 --> 35:23.555
You paid a shitload
for your house, right?

35:23.622 --> 35:25.991
Yeah.
Right, right? Well,
you wanna look out the window...

35:26.057 --> 35:29.228
and see a bunch of guys
French-kissin' or havin'
some kind of naked pool party...

35:29.295 --> 35:31.330
with your kids around?

35:31.397 --> 35:35.167
Shit no!
I pay that kind of money
for a house,

35:35.234 --> 35:38.437
I don't want to live
next to somebody
I don't want to live next to.

35:38.504 --> 35:40.772
It's my right
as an American citizen.

35:40.839 --> 35:44.042
But I have met the Oxenbergs.
They have a kid.

35:44.109 --> 35:45.977
You know, they're harmless.
Doug.

35:46.044 --> 35:50.115
I sell that house to them,
I lose millions of dollars.

35:50.182 --> 35:53.185
End of story.
I gotta go.

35:53.252 --> 35:55.987
This nice girl's gonna finish
wrappin' me up here.

35:56.054 --> 35:58.224
[ Line Disconnects ]
Hugh, just--

36:03.362 --> 36:05.897
You don't have
to do this, Wayne.

36:08.334 --> 36:10.369
Dahlia,
you don't understand.

36:27.353 --> 36:29.288
Hey.
What's up?

36:29.355 --> 36:30.689
Hey, Di.
Hey.

36:30.756 --> 36:34.159
Gettin' some gum.
Eighty-one cents.

36:34.226 --> 36:36.795
Out of 10.

36:39.698 --> 36:42.368
Here you go.

36:42.434 --> 36:44.470
I really don't want
all this change, man.
I'm sorry.

36:44.536 --> 36:48.307
You can probably use it
more than I can. Mind if
I give you 10 ones for a 10?

36:48.374 --> 36:50.476
Whatever.
Yeah?

36:52.878 --> 36:56.147
Thanks. I really don't wanna
carry around all those bills,
you know what I mean?

36:56.214 --> 36:59.551
Cael?
You know what?

36:59.618 --> 37:02.020
Um, I'm not thirsty.
Let's just-- Let's-Let's go.

37:02.087 --> 37:03.555
Well, I-I am.
Just put it back.

37:03.622 --> 37:05.857
Wait. Hold on.
What's-- What is the rush?

37:05.924 --> 37:08.460
Whoa, whoa.
You gave me too much, dude.

37:08.527 --> 37:10.662
Oh, shit. I'm--
I'm an idiot, man.

37:10.729 --> 37:13.765
I'm sorry.
Is that Witchblade?
I love Witchblade.

37:13.832 --> 37:16.568
I'm more of
a Spawn guy myself.
Spawn's for freaks, man.

37:16.635 --> 37:17.903
Ah.
[ Di Di ]
Cael.

37:17.969 --> 37:21.039
I'm sorry.
I'm holdin' up the line.

37:21.106 --> 37:24.776
I'm talkin' too much.
Why don't I just give you
this for the 20?

37:24.843 --> 37:27.679
- Is he doin' what
I think he's doin'?
- You know what? I don't care.

37:27.746 --> 37:29.615
But I'm not gonna stick around
and watch this. Come on.
Thanks.

37:33.685 --> 37:36.322
Thanks, man.
All right, now.

37:37.689 --> 37:39.591
[ Beeps ]

37:42.260 --> 37:44.430
[ High-pitched Tone ]

37:53.572 --> 37:55.507
Next.

38:01.279 --> 38:04.750
Cael?
Where are you?

38:08.354 --> 38:12.057
Oh. There was a man.

38:12.123 --> 38:16.928
What man?
I made some calls.

38:19.264 --> 38:23.402
[ Di Di ]
Cael? Cael?

38:25.904 --> 38:28.940
- What's wrong with you?
- With what?

38:29.007 --> 38:32.110
Why did you short-count
the sales guy?
You don't need the kale.

38:32.177 --> 38:36.982
Just keepin' up
my skills, Di.
You could have been arrested.

38:37.048 --> 38:39.017
You did it in front of Eric.

38:39.084 --> 38:44.289
I did it in front of Eric?
Eric is clueless.

38:44.356 --> 38:47.659
He knew exactly what
you were doing, Cael.

38:47.726 --> 38:50.696
Luckily, he just thinks
you're a total asshole.
Good.

38:50.762 --> 38:54.566
This is who I am.
I'm all right with that.

38:54.633 --> 38:58.470
Fine. You know what?
Be whoever you wanna be, Cael,
but don't screw this up for me.

38:58.537 --> 39:00.906
These people--

39:00.972 --> 39:03.842
your boyfriend,
the teachers, the neighbors--

39:03.909 --> 39:07.713
I don't get it.
Why do you give a shit
what they think of you?

39:07.779 --> 39:10.782
Because I like them, Cael.
Okay.

39:10.849 --> 39:15.487
How many of them
will be there
for you in the end?

39:15.554 --> 39:19.725
When it really counts, Di?
When all this goes to shit?

39:19.791 --> 39:21.627
Not one.

39:21.693 --> 39:25.664
You know,
I used to look up to you.

39:25.731 --> 39:27.699
And now, I don't even know
who you are anymore.

39:27.766 --> 39:31.136
You don't know
who I am anymore?

39:33.238 --> 39:35.040
I'm not the one
who's changed, Di.

39:35.106 --> 39:37.676
I'm not the one
who's turning my back
on my family...

39:37.743 --> 39:40.979
'cause I'm ashamed
of who I am.

39:59.197 --> 40:03.702
All rise.
Honorable Judge Pearline
now presides.

40:03.769 --> 40:05.604
Okay.

40:05.671 --> 40:09.875
In the case of
Oxenberg, Thomas v. Panco, Inc.

40:09.941 --> 40:14.480
Your Honor, Douglas Rich
for the accused--
for the defendant.

40:16.882 --> 40:20.118
May it please the court--
Your Honor,

40:20.185 --> 40:23.522
state and federal laws
prohibit discrimination...

40:23.589 --> 40:25.591
on the basis of race,
religion and gender.

40:25.657 --> 40:28.660
However--
[ Judge Pearline ] Let me
stop you right there, Mr. Rich.

40:28.727 --> 40:33.264
- Your Honor?
- I have read your arguments,
Mr. Rich, and you are right.

40:33.331 --> 40:37.869
They don't have a case.
Your summary judgment
is granted. Case is dismissed.

40:37.936 --> 40:39.938
[ Gavel Raps ]
Bailiff, what's next?

40:40.005 --> 40:43.108
[ Spectators Murmuring ]
That's it?

40:43.174 --> 40:47.312
You won your argument, Mr. Rich.
Do you want a medal?

40:47.378 --> 40:49.815
Bailiff?
[ Rapping Gavel ]

40:49.881 --> 40:55.053
[ Bailiff ]
Case number 0270595.
Atkinson v. Layton.

40:58.524 --> 41:00.992
[ Chattering ]

41:05.564 --> 41:07.666
What are you doin'?
Don't you know I fired you?

41:07.733 --> 41:09.735
I don't need
to get paid.

41:09.801 --> 41:13.338
You can't just put plants
in my yard. I told you Everett
doesn't like me having friends.

41:13.404 --> 41:16.474
Then we won't be "friends."

41:16.542 --> 41:19.244
Dale, you need to go.

41:19.310 --> 41:22.280
I think you're a treasure.

41:22.347 --> 41:24.349
I'm gonna call
the police on you.

41:24.415 --> 41:27.953
- Go ahead.
- I'll call my husband.

41:29.721 --> 41:32.791
God, you are beautiful.

41:32.858 --> 41:36.995
I am gonna paint your house
from top to bottom.

41:37.062 --> 41:39.064
Please go.

41:39.130 --> 41:41.132
You want me to go?

41:42.568 --> 41:45.971
Or do you want me
to move in?

41:46.037 --> 41:49.908
Everett hears everything
that goes on in that house.

41:49.975 --> 41:52.778
I think he's got cameras.
I think he's got me bugged.

41:52.844 --> 41:55.547
Then I'll move into
the pool house!

41:55.614 --> 41:57.583
[ Softly ]
I'll be discreet.

42:00.151 --> 42:03.622
Dale, you are really cute,
but I think
you might be crazy.

42:03.689 --> 42:07.292
[ Chuckling ]

42:07.358 --> 42:09.995
I'm gonna be
your handyman.

42:12.363 --> 42:15.767
I'm gonna come in
real handy.

42:18.436 --> 42:21.539
His back is broken.
Broken?

42:21.607 --> 42:24.275
But apparently only enough
to put pressure
on his spinal cord.

42:24.342 --> 42:27.579
The only way to remove that
is to operate.
Then why haven't you?

42:27.646 --> 42:32.183
I thought you understood.
He may not be strong enough
to survive it.

42:32.250 --> 42:34.986
And under the circumstances,
I couldn't assume
the responsibility...

42:35.053 --> 42:38.389
without your consent.
My consent?
Well, why mine?

42:38.456 --> 42:42.928
You're his next of kin,
aren't you? The only way
to remove that is to operate.

42:42.994 --> 42:47.733
Then why haven't you?
What are we gonna do
with you, Mama?

42:47.799 --> 42:51.637
There was a man.
Oh, there's always a man.

42:51.703 --> 42:55.240
One of life's tragedies.

42:55.306 --> 42:59.310
We fall in love,
then we have to deal with
all the shit that comes with it.

42:59.377 --> 43:03.148
Now, wait a minute.
I'm not going to be held
responsible if that boy dies.

43:03.214 --> 43:07.518
Why do you think Cherien
turned out such a bitch?

43:07.585 --> 43:09.988
Was it 'cause of you?

43:10.055 --> 43:12.223
Was it somethin'
you did or didn't do?

43:21.232 --> 43:26.337
I feel like a crap mother
most of the time.

43:26.404 --> 43:28.807
I was two years
in the slammer.

43:28.874 --> 43:31.409
Did a lot of drugs.

43:31.476 --> 43:34.045
Did a lot of bad things.

43:34.112 --> 43:36.815
I ain't gonna win
no good parent award,
you know?

43:41.186 --> 43:43.822
I love my kids
more than the world.

43:46.892 --> 43:49.260
No one told me how to do it.

43:54.800 --> 43:57.402
Boy, I wish you could
tell me how.

44:07.045 --> 44:10.248
I've been clean two days.

44:10.315 --> 44:12.283
I guess that's somethin'.

44:32.237 --> 44:34.139
[ Door Opens ]

44:35.273 --> 44:38.744
I'm lockin' up now, sir.
Oh, right, Officer.

45:11.676 --> 45:15.180
What's this?
It's a cup of tea.

45:15.246 --> 45:17.615
Thought it might help
if you were gonna be
up late studying.

45:17.682 --> 45:20.451
Thanks, Mom.

45:21.920 --> 45:24.790
Trust don't come easy,
Di Di.

45:24.856 --> 45:26.792
I know that
better than anyone.

45:29.594 --> 45:31.729
I can wait.

45:33.999 --> 45:35.967
Mom?

45:37.702 --> 45:39.504
I never slept with Eric.

45:45.043 --> 45:48.113
Oh.

45:48.179 --> 45:50.115
Okay.

46:05.763 --> 46:07.933
Hi.

46:09.067 --> 46:11.903
Hi.

46:11.970 --> 46:15.974
I don't know how to be
myself here, Wayne.

46:19.510 --> 46:21.612
Sometimes I think I do.

46:21.679 --> 46:24.415
Then it all gets
messed up.

46:24.482 --> 46:30.121
I mess it up,
and I end up
blaming everyone.

46:31.356 --> 46:33.158
In camp,

46:33.224 --> 46:38.229
there were rules,
traditions.

46:38.296 --> 46:41.833
It just kinda
makes sense.

46:41.900 --> 46:44.535
Now that we're here,

46:46.337 --> 46:48.306
I don't know
what the rules are.

46:50.041 --> 46:55.713
Neither do I, baby.
Neither do I.

46:55.780 --> 46:57.883
I guess we're making
them up as we go.

47:00.485 --> 47:02.320
I was thinking.

47:05.356 --> 47:07.425
You still wanna find
a cold river somewhere?

47:11.762 --> 47:14.299
'Cause I do.

47:25.243 --> 47:28.179
It's not exactly
a river.

47:29.347 --> 47:31.482
Those rocks
aren't even real.

47:33.384 --> 47:35.820
It's all we got.

47:35.887 --> 47:40.325
How'd it go in court today?
I won.

47:43.361 --> 47:45.230
I'm sorry.

47:45.296 --> 47:48.733
[ Man ]
* I've been touched *

47:48.799 --> 47:54.005
* Now I don't believe it *

47:54.072 --> 47:59.477
* Moving us closer now *

48:02.247 --> 48:05.716
* Here's my touch *

48:05.783 --> 48:10.421
* Now, please receive it *

48:10.488 --> 48:16.227
* Let's do some more
touching now *

48:18.429 --> 48:24.635
* Let's do some more
touching now **
